 if you wish to continue using windows xp and would like to use one of our advanced format drives you will need to use a thirdparty software to align the partitions so that the os may communicate with the drive properly please note that attempting to run an alignment tool on an encrypted drive you will corrupt and lose your data if you must do so decrypt your drive first run the alignment and then reencrypt your drive hgst suggests two tools for alignment of k advanced format drives acronis disk director httpwwwacroniscomhomecomputingproductsdiskdirector paragon partition alignment httpwwwparagonsoftwarecomhomepartitionalignment additional productivity tools for oems resellers and system integrators are available through hgsts partners first program linkedin twitter hgst blog youtube facebook productshard drives solidstate drives platforms systems affiliate brandstouro external storage touro cloud backup solutionsby use casebackup recovery  archive private  hybrid clouds database acceleration virtualization by industrycloud service providers financial services healthcare  life sciences oil  gas telecommunications media  entertainment other enterprise data centers supporthard drive support solidstate drive support software support systems support platforms support product security partnerspartners first program enterprise partner program partner alliance companycompany info executive team careers corporate citizenship global footprint investor relations innovation center resources public relationsmedia room press releases news and reviews events and webinars blog   hgst inc site map trademarks privacy policy legal policy cookie policy contact us  hgst skip to main content ☰ contact us how to buy english 繁体 简体  한국어 deutsch français русский productshard drives solidstate solutions platforms systems solutionssolutions for your industrycloud service providers financial services healthcare  life sciences oil  gas telecommunications media  entertainment other enterprise da